snippet.textDisplay:
Okay i want to chat about Salah - there is this mis information going around showing salah to be the one with most assist/key passes etc. This is done by bringing up stats starting from begining of 17/18 when he first joined us,
including that amazing first season where all he turned touched to goals
and was assisting and scoring multiple times a game for fun!

That was never in doubt - the problem is since half way through last
season, salah has become incredibly selfish, several times every game
he has an option to put somebody in but goes for the shot and more times
that not it ends up scuffed wide or tamely at the keeper.

If you take on his assists or key passes since mid way through last season
and dont sugar coat it adding his first season - its a totally
different story.

The guy is incredibly predicatable, every defender knows hes going to cut in from the wing and try to bend it in the corner!

Yes it comes off every few games, but for a guy who finds himself in a
great goalscoring position multiple times a game, it is absolutly
criminal the amount of goals he squanders for the team - absolutly
criminal!

All the best strikers miss sitters and have a rutheless streak but salah is not a natural finisher he needs about 6 chances to score!
